<span class="subhead">CES' Newest Venue Contributes to Largest Show Floor in Show's History </span>

<br><br>While the Las Vegas Convention Center holds the title of biggest CES facililty, the show's newest venue may just come out holding the title of coolest things to do. The The Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian is&nbsp;the new home to the CES keynotes,&nbsp;Innovations honorees, <A href="/attendees/markets/hpaht.asp">high-performance audio and home theater</A> exhibits and largest concentration of TechZones.<BR><BR>Some of the biggest names in the consumer electronics and content industries have been taking&nbsp;the <A href="/attendees/conferences/keynotes.asp">keynote</A> stage in The Venetian's Palazzo Ballroom.&nbsp;Speakers include Microsoft's Bill Gates, Motorola's Ed Zander, Disney's Robert Iger, Dell's Michael Dell and CBS' Leslie Moonves.<BR><BR>Showcasing the latest industry trends and emerging technologies, The Anytime, Anywhere TechArena, sponsored by Sling Media and located at the Sands/Venetian, will feature the latest in portable content shifting devices, and also will house The Download, ExpressCard, IPTV and Podcasting TechZones. Additional <A href="/attendees/show_floor/techzones/default.asp">TechZones</A> making a splash at the International CES include the Gaming TechZone, showcasing the latest PC and console gaming developments, and the Robotics TechZone, which will debut the latest in robotics trends.<BR><BR>Additionally, the highly regarded <A href="/attendees/awards/innovations/rd_2007honorees.asp">Innovations Design and Engineering showcase</A> returns where the International CES honors the best designed and engineered products new to the market. The Innovations 2007 Showcase will be on display throughout CES at the Sands/Venetian (booth #68747) and also includes a stage for honoree presentations.<BR><BR>Navigation between the CES venues and around Las Vegas is also a priority for CES.&nbsp;CES encourages use of its two <A href="/attendees/travel/shuttle.asp">shuttle bus routes</A>: the Sands/Venetian hotel shuttle between each official CES hotel and the Sands/Venetian Express, which will travel between the Sands/Venetian and the LVCC.

