<span class="subhead">U.S. Secretary of Commerce speaks at the 2007 International CES.</span>

<br><br>U.S. Secretary of Commerce Carlos M. Gutierrez will offer opening remarks at this year’s International SuperSession. Here’s why this matters to you: As the voice of business in government, Gutierrez’s top priority is opening international markets to U.S. companies.&nbsp;<BR><BR>Hear his take on current regulatory issues and where he sees technology policy heading – both issues&nbsp;that pertain to almost every attendee and exhibitor getting ready to head to Vegas in January. His comments&nbsp;set the stage for an active discussion by senior officials from Japan, Brazil and the United States on the most competitive policies supporting industry growth and sales of high tech products and services. <BR><BR>International SuperSession:&nbsp;1:30-2:30 p.m. Tuesday, January 9, LVCC, North Hall N262. <A href="/attendees/conferences/supersessions.asp">More.</A><BR>

